    • Method Detail

      • get

        public V get(io.fluo.api.client.SnapshotBase tx,
             K key)
        This method will retrieve the current value for key and any outstanding updates and combine them using the configured Combiner. The result from the combiner is returned.

      • update

        public void update(io.fluo.api.client.TransactionBase tx,
                   Map<K,V> updates)
        Queues updates for a collision free map. These updates will be made by an Observer executing another transaction. This method will not collide with other transaction queuing updates for the same keys.
        Parameters:
        tx - This transaction will be used to make the updates.
        updates - The keys in the map should correspond to keys in the collision free map being updated. The values in the map will be queued for updating.

      • getInstance

      • getInitializer

        public static <K2,V2> CollisionFreeMap.Initializer<K2,V2> getInitializer(String mapId,
                                                                         int numBuckets,
                                                                         SimpleSerializer serializer)
        A @link CollisionFreeMap stores data in its own data format in the Fluo table. When initializing a Fluo table with something like Map Reduce or Spark, data will need to be written in this format. Thats the purpose of this method, it provide a simple class that can do this conversion.

      • configure

        public static void configure(io.fluo.api.config.FluoConfiguration fluoConfig,
                             CollisionFreeMap.Options opts)
        This method configures a collision free map for use. It must be called before initializing Fluo.

      • getTableOptimizations

        public static Pirtos getTableOptimizations(org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration appConfig)
        Return suggested Fluo table optimizations for all previously configured collision free maps.
        Parameters:
        appConfig - Must pass in the application configuration obtained from FluoClient.getAppConfiguration() or FluoConfiguration.getAppConfiguration()
